          "Your family was always there for you. When you were diagnosed with bone cancer as a young child, your parents spent long hours at your side during grueling chemotherapy sessions.  Surgery after surgery drained their resources and the debt kept them working multiple jobs long after you'd entered remission.  Your gratitude pushed you academically and physically. You  excelled at multiple sports eventually winning scholarships in soccer, wrestling and target shooting. While it was unlikely that you'd ever have been an Olympian it was still a possibility when they came for you.  The Sabbat were at war and your embrace was one of a multitude.  That first night has little purchase in your memory but you do know that your parents did not survive.  The guilt that you may have killed them weighs heavily on your mind and you hope to adopt a Path that will free you from these feelings."
